The proton conductivity of the prepared membrane was calculated using a four-electrode conductivity cell connected to a potentiostat/galvanostat (WonATech) operating over a frequency range of 1 MHz down to 50 Hz. The membranes (1 cm × 4 cm in size) must be soaked in water for 24 h for the conductivity readings under the fully hydrated state. The potentiostat was run to obtain the graph of voltage versus current. The gradient of the straight line is the membrane resistance. Scheme 1 presents the cell of the proton conductivity test. The proton conductivity can be calculated using the following formula:3σ=LRWT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
